</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="152.[189,1399,1850,2017]" lastBlockId="154.[189,1399,267,364]" lastPageId="154" lastPageNumber="155" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
Distribution: Nearctic and Neotropical regions. Host plants are herbaceous and woody dicots. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Say, 1830)" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[189,741,1885,1912]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphytopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutus" subGenus="Cloanthanus">
<emphasis box="[189,345,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Scaphytopius</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[361,511,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Cloanthanus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[526,603,1886,1911]" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">acutus</emphasis>
(Say, 1830)
</taxonomicName>
is a vector of alfalfa witches’ broom, eastern and western X-diseases of peach, little cherry, soybean bud proliferation, clover phyllody, and western strain of North American aster yellows. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Van Duzee, 1910)" baseAuthorityName="Van Duzee" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[477,992,1956,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraphlepsius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irroratus" subGenus="Convelinus">
<emphasis box="[477,499,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">S.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[515,647,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Convelinus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[663,768,1957,1982]" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">irroratus</emphasis>
(Van Duzee, 1910)
</taxonomicName>
vectors the western strain of North American aster yellows. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Provancher, 1889)" baseAuthorityName="Provancher" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[488,1084,1991,2017]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphytopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magdalensis" subGenus="Cloanthanus">
<emphasis box="[488,510,1991,2017]" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">S.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[530,680,1991,2017]" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Cloanthanus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[700,847,1991,2017]" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">magdalensis</emphasis>
(Provancher, 1889)
</taxonomicName>
transmits blueberry stunt. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Osborn, 1923)" baseAuthorityName="Osborn" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[189,695,267,294]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphytopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="154" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuliginosus" subGenus="Convelinus">
<emphasis box="[189,211,268,294]" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">S.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[229,361,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Convelinus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[379,508,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">fuliginosus</emphasis>
(Osborn, 1923)
</taxonomicName>
is a vector of machismo disease of legumes in 
<collectingCountry box="[1258,1348,267,293]" name="Mexico" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and South America. 
<taxonomicName authority="(DeLong, 1943)" baseAuthorityName="DeLong" baseAuthorityYear="1943" box="[379,854,303,329]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphytopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="154" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitridus" subGenus="Convelinus">
<emphasis box="[379,401,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">S.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[418,550,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Convelinus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[567,658,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">nitridus</emphasis>
(DeLong, 1943)
</taxonomicName>
is a vector of western X-disease of stonefruits and celery in North America.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
